There's a little airport in Kehoe.

232
00:28:49.240 --> 00:28:51.356
He flies in with the coke
and out with the money.

233
00:28:51.440 --> 00:28:52.430
What does he look like?

234
00:28:53.360 --> 00:28:54.509
He looks like a Santa.

235
00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:58.640
No! Come on. please.
You don't have to do that.

236
00:28:59.040 --> 00:29:00.474
Come on. please.

237
00:29:09.280 --> 00:29:10.350
Elway or Manning?

238
00:29:15.080 --> 00:29:16.070
What?

239
00:29:16.640 --> 00:29:19.871
Greatest quarterback ever.
Elway or Manning?

240
00:29:26.600 --> 00:29:27.590
Elway.

241
00:30:10.240 --> 00:30:12.470
Did you know Kyle had a Facebook?

242
00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:18.754
Do you know his favorite band?

243
00:30:23.280 --> 00:30:25.556
He posted his favorite movies.
do you know those?

244
00:30:30.360 --> 00:30:33.000
What'd the two of you talk about
on your damn hunting trips?

245
00:30:38.680 --> 00:30:39.670
Hunting.

246
00:30:53.240 --> 00:30:54.230
Damn it.

247
00:30:54.680 --> 00:30:55.670
Goddamn.

248
00:31:03.560 --> 00:31:04.595
Damn it!

249
00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:11.952
- That's the fourth gym bag you've lost.
- Yeah. but who's counting. right?

250
00:31:14.600 --> 00:31:16.113
You might find this hard to believe

251
00:31:16.200 --> 00:31:19.158
but I've got more important things to do
than keep track of gym bags.

252
00:31:19.240 --> 00:31:21.470
Like earning the money to pay for them.

253
00:31:22.480 --> 00:31:23.470
Tell you what...

254
00:31:23.920 --> 00:31:25.035
why don't you take this

255
00:31:25.840 --> 00:31:28.992
and buy him every single
goddamn gym bag he'll ever need.

256
00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:30.630
Does that work for you?

257
00:31:34.800 --> 00:31:35.790
All right.

258
00:31:36.560 --> 00:31:37.755
Well. that's for you.

259
00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:41.839
- Tell me this is a joke.
- No.

260
00:31:41.960 --> 00:31:44.554
That's Ryan's new diet.
And you're gonna follow it to the letter.

261
00:31:44.960 --> 00:31:47.839
Breakfast: grass-fed beef.
asparagus. cashews.

262
00:31:47.920 --> 00:31:49.638
Lunch. the same. Dinner. the same.

263
00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:51.751
Yeah. that's on Mondays.
Tuesday it rotates.

264
00:31:51.840 --> 00:31:53.274
Chicken. broccoli and almonds.

265
00:31:53.560 --> 00:31:54.994
For breakfast. lunch and dinner?

266
00:31:56.720 --> 00:31:58.870
You want our son to eat the same thing
three times a day?

267
00:31:58.960 --> 00:32:01.679
Eighty percent of our immune system
starts in the gut.

268
00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:05.073
Keep it simple in the gut.
you get to live a long life.

269
00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:07.310
A week on this diet
and he'll wanna kill himself.

270
00:32:08.280 --> 00:32:09.475
And I'll help him do it.

271
00:32:09.560 --> 00:32:11.233
You know what. you should be grateful.

272
00:32:12.320 --> 00:32:13.549
My dad started my day

273
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:15.950
with half a grapefruit
and three lines of primo coke.

274
00:32:16.600 --> 00:32:18.352
"Breakfast of champions." he called it.

275
00:32:18.440 --> 00:32:21.637
And now your son can't look at a candy bar
without breaking into hives.

276
00:32:22.640 --> 00:32:24.517
Congratulations. you've broken the cycle.

277
00:32:26.160 --> 00:32:27.195
And to think...

278
00:32:31.160 --> 00:32:33.436
I used to love the mouth on you.

279
00:32:34.760 --> 00:32:36.080
I've spoken to my lawyer.

280
00:32:37.240 --> 00:32:39.880
We want a new arrangement.
Ten days with me. four with you.

281
00:32:41.560 --> 00:32:42.550
Huh.

282
00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:47.839
Here's my counter offer.
Fourteen days with me and none with you.

283
00:32:47.920 --> 00:32:49.957
Let's see what your lawyer
thinks about that.

284
00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:56.838
- Morning. Aya.
- Hey. Mustang.

285
00:33:03.800 --> 00:33:06.110
They say Limbo's disappeared.

286
00:33:21.440 --> 00:33:23.238
Don't worry about it. he'll get over it.

287
00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:27.995
Is that Mozart?

288
00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:32.914
Bach. You can always tell Bach
because he's really mathematical.

289
00:33:34.480 --> 00:33:36.630
- Is he the one with all the kids?
- Yeah. 20.

290
00:33:40.560 --> 00:33:42.517
It's a wonder he found
any time to compose.

291
00:33:43.560 --> 00:33:45.437
I need your help with my fantasy football.

292
00:33:46.480 --> 00:33:48.471
I can't... I can't win a game.

293
00:33:52.280 --> 00:33:53.270
Playing for money?

294
00:33:55.440 --> 00:33:57.431
Yeah. of course I'm playing for money.

295
00:34:00.320 --> 00:34:02.675
You got four Cleveland Browns
on your team.

296
00:34:03.800 --> 00:34:04.995
Well. they're my home team.

297
00:34:06.320 --> 00:34:07.640
What's a man without loyalty?

298
00:34:10.880 --> 00:34:11.995
I can't help you.

299
00:35:54.720 --> 00:35:56.950
Hey. there's not enough room to pass.

300
00:35:57.040 --> 00:35:59.919
I was wondering if you'd back down
to the turnoff?

301
00:36:07.640 --> 00:36:08.994
Any chance you could back up?

302
00:36:12.720 --> 00:36:15.473
Um. just between you and me. right?

303
00:36:16.360 --> 00:36:17.589
Me. you and frosty.

304
00:36:19.440 --> 00:36:20.271
Sure.

305
00:36:29.640 --> 00:36:33.395
You have no clue
who you're messing with. man.

306
00:36:33.760 --> 00:36:34.830
Who am I messing with?

307
00:36:37.240 --> 00:36:39.356
You're dust. pal.

308
00:36:47.800 --> 00:36:48.790
Tell me.

309
00:36:51.040 --> 00:36:53.509
You're wasting your time.

310
00:37:07.440 --> 00:37:10.478
Are you tired. old man?

311
00:37:14.360 --> 00:37:15.350
Yeah.

312
00:37:41.880 --> 00:37:45.794
<i>♪ >A' He's gone ♪</i>

313
00:37:45.880 --> 00:37:49.919
<i>♪ Two thousand miles ♪</i>

314
00:37:51.080 --> 00:37:52.912
<i>♪ It's very far ♪</i>

315
00:37:56.440 --> 00:38:00.229
<i>♪ The snow is falling down ♪</i>

316
00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:03.958
<i>♪ Gets colder day by day ♪</i>

317
00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:07.670
<i>♪ I miss you ♪</i>

318
00:38:11.840 --> 00:38:14.400
<i>♪ The children will sing ♪</i>

319
00:38:14.720 --> 00:38:18.793
<i>♪ He'll be back
At Christmas time ♪</i>

320
00:38:27.560 --> 00:38:28.709
Grace?

321
00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.229
Grace?

322
00:39:52.640 --> 00:39:54.119
What are you doing here?

323
00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.035
Kyle's dead.

324
00:39:59.120 --> 00:40:00.110
Somebody killed him.

325
00:40:01.560 --> 00:40:03.039
What's that got to do with me?

326
00:40:04.520 --> 00:40:05.590
Can I come in?

327
00:40:14.160 --> 00:40:16.595
Better take your shoes off.
She'll skin you alive.

328
00:40:18.960 --> 00:40:20.712
I'm going to make some phone calls.

329
00:40:20.800 --> 00:40:22.154
Find out what happened to Kyle.

330
00:40:56.760 --> 00:40:59.115
She thinks you're
one of the guys from the old days.

331
00:40:59.840 --> 00:41:00.875
Don't worry about her.

332
00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:06.918
Kyle. He got mixed up with some clown
by the name of Dante.

333
00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:09.310
And they stole a kilo of coke from Viking.

334
00:41:09.840 --> 00:41:12.309
- Who's Viking?
- Drug dealer. A big one.

335
00:41:13.160 --> 00:41:16.357
- You know him?
- Yeah. when he was a snot-nosed kid.

336
00:41:17.240 --> 00:41:20.551
- I knew his old man. Bullitt.
- Dad knew him. too?

337
00:41:20.640 --> 00:41:22.916
Whenever Bullitt had rough stuff
to be done.

338
00:41:23.040 --> 00:41:25.316
Dad was his go-to guy. After Dad. me.

339
00:41:26.000 --> 00:41:27.354
And then Viking took over.

340
00:41:28.240 --> 00:41:30.151
Viking's a whole different breed.

341
00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:31.794
He likes hurting people.

342
00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:36.113
I'm gonna kill him. Brock.

343
00:41:39.200 --> 00:41:40.315
Sure you are.

344
00:41:41.960 --> 00:41:43.712
What makes you think you can kill a man?

345
00:41:48.400 --> 00:41:49.390
I've...

346
00:41:50.160 --> 00:41:51.992
I've killed three of his guys.

347
00:41:53.800 --> 00:41:55.313
What did you do with the bodies?

348
00:41:56.120 --> 00:41:58.714
Wrapped them in chicken wire.
threw them on the gorge.

349
00:42:01.200 --> 00:42:03.555
- Chicken wire?
- Yeah. to let the fish get at them.

350
00:42:04.200 --> 00:42:05.759
They'll eat the flesh off the bones.

351
00:42:06.600 --> 00:42:08.671
So the bodies don't fill
with gas and rise.

352
00:42:08.960 --> 00:42:10.633
They stay at the bottom.

353
00:42:12.720 --> 00:42:16.350
- Where did you learn that?
- I read it in a crime novel.

354
00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:32.674
- He is my brother.
- Brother?

355
00:42:33.560 --> 00:42:34.550
My ass.

356
00:42:39.960 --> 00:42:42.600
I know.

357
00:42:49.760 --> 00:42:51.433
- Maybe I should...
- Shut up.

358
00:42:58.400 --> 00:42:59.720
You stay out of trouble.

359
00:43:03.680 --> 00:43:05.273
The things we do for love. huh?

360
00:43:06.440 --> 00:43:08.795
She was skimming the till
at a massage parlor.

361
00:43:08.880 --> 00:43:11.315
They sent me to beat the shit
out of her. Instead...

362
00:43:12.400 --> 00:43:13.390
How's Grace?

363
00:43:15.520 --> 00:43:16.715
She left.

364
00:43:17.720 --> 00:43:19.836
The lady's got good timing.
I'll give her that.

365
00:43:19.920 --> 00:43:21.638
How do I find this Viking?

366
00:43:22.760 --> 00:43:23.591
You don't.

367
00:43:25.080 --> 00:43:27.674
You've gone as far up
the ladder as you're gonna go.

368
00:43:27.760 --> 00:43:28.955
We'll see.

369
00:43:30.560 --> 00:43:33.916
One guy can disappear.
Two? I don't think so.

370
00:43:34.000 --> 00:43:36.560
Three? With ten keys of coke?

371
00:43:37.760 --> 00:43:39.592
Maybe they were
all in it together.

372
00:43:47.240 --> 00:43:49.800
You think three of my dealers
ran out on me?

373
00:43:50.960 --> 00:43:53.270
That would make me the worst judge
of character in the Rockies.

374
00:43:53.400 --> 00:43:54.435
that's your theory?

375
00:43:57.760 --> 00:43:58.750
- No.
- No.

376
00:44:03.400 --> 00:44:06.119
It was those goddamn Indians.

377
00:44:06.200 --> 00:44:08.794
This is all my father's fault
for getting into bed with them.

378
00:44:09.160 --> 00:44:10.230
I'm sorry. the Indians?

379
00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:12.357
When Viking's father
was first getting started.

380
00:44:12.440 --> 00:44:14.431
he made a deal with an Indian
named White Bull.

381
00:44:14.920 --> 00:44:17.196
He supplied him. White Bull dealt
on the reservation.

382
00:44:17.280 --> 00:44:19.396
Until White Bull wanted more turf.

383
00:44:19.480 --> 00:44:21.790
So he tossed White Bull
a few piece of crap towns.

384
00:44:22.080 --> 00:44:23.115
Like Kehoe.

385
00:44:23.440 --> 00:44:26.876
And Kehoe builds a ski resort.
Turns it into a gold mine.

386
00:44:27.480 --> 00:44:29.949
What's the one thing history's taught us?

387
00:44:30.400 --> 00:44:33.472
You keep those Indians on the reservation.

388
00:44:34.560 --> 00:44:37.552
Those Indians.
they're always wanting more.

389
00:44:37.920 --> 00:44:40.036
Because they think the turf
was theirs all along.

390
00:44:40.680 --> 00:44:42.478
Might kinda have a point there. right.

391
00:44:56.920 --> 00:44:58.911
White Bull gave this to my father...

392
00:45:00.320 --> 00:45:02.118
the day they shook on their deal.

393
00:45:04.000 --> 00:45:05.070
Yeah.

394
00:45:06.520 --> 00:45:08.033
It's time we give it back to him.

395
00:45:16.040 --> 00:45:18.475
- What can I do for you two?
- You could sit down with us.

396
00:45:18.560 --> 00:45:19.709
Tell us your story.

397
00:45:19.960 --> 00:45:22.634
- I got other customers.
- Yeah. that's funny.

398
00:45:22.720 --> 00:45:24.074
All I can see in here is you.

399
00:45:25.280 --> 00:45:26.953
Please tell me you work nights.

400
00:45:27.720 --> 00:45:29.358
Thursdays. Why?

401
00:45:29.440 --> 00:45:32.353
You look this good in sunlight.
I gotta see you after dark.

402
00:45:32.440 --> 00:45:35.831
Eggs. bacon. pancakes.

403
00:45:35.960 --> 00:45:37.030
And for you?

404
00:45:37.600 --> 00:45:40.114
Surprise me.

405
00:45:41.280 --> 00:45:42.270
Okay.

406
00:45:43.760 --> 00:45:46.673
I was 13 when my dad kicked it.
You know his last words to me?

407
00:45:47.160 --> 00:45:49.629
"Try to bang every waitress
who ever serves you."

408
00:45:55.640 --> 00:45:58.439
This Indian is
taking forever to show up.

409
00:46:03.960 --> 00:46:07.112
So. tell me
about this motel trick of yours.

410
00:46:07.720 --> 00:46:08.710
Twenty bucks.

411
00:46:11.320 --> 00:46:13.072
It's not a trick. all right.

412
00:46:13.640 --> 00:46:15.199
It's a beautiful invention.

413
00:46:15.280 --> 00:46:17.635
It's an invention Steve Jobs
would have been proud of.

414
00:46:17.720 --> 00:46:19.119
- Steve Jobs. huh?
- That's right.

415
00:46:19.200 --> 00:46:22.272
You know what made that guy
such a genius? Simplicity.

416
00:46:22.360 --> 00:46:24.033
- Let's hear it already.
- All right.

417
00:46:25.080 --> 00:46:28.152
I stay in motels 100 nights a year. right.

418
00:46:28.240 --> 00:46:29.674
First thing. every morning.

419
00:46:30.120 --> 00:46:32.157
I hang a "clean the room" sign
on the doorknob.

420
00:46:32.240 --> 00:46:33.992
Maid sees the sign. she opens the door.

421
00:46:34.440 --> 00:46:36.909
Now. pay attention to the details here.

422
00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:38.752
All the hard thought behind them.

423
00:46:39.600 --> 00:46:43.389
I'm lying on top of the covers.
stone naked.

424
00:46:44.640 --> 00:46:47.712
First crucial part.
I look into the maid's eyes. all right?

425
00:46:47.800 --> 00:46:49.950
If I don't.
she backs right outta that door.

426
00:46:50.040 --> 00:46:51.758
It's over before it even starts.

427
00:46:53.080 --> 00:46:56.436
I take the twenty.
I lay it right on my Jimmy.

428
00:46:56.520 --> 00:46:57.954
- Boom.
- Just a twenty?

429
00:46:58.600 --> 00:47:01.956
Maids make $8.35 an hour.
and they've got miserable lives too.

430
00:47:02.040 --> 00:47:04.031
That's the totally underrated part
of this.

431
00:47:04.120 --> 00:47:05.474
The ball is completely in her court.

432
00:47:05.560 --> 00:47:07.710
She could back out of that door
no harm. no foul.

433
00:47:07.960 --> 00:47:10.600
Or... she could come and get it.

434
00:47:13.200 --> 00:47:15.589
- What's your success rate?
- Thirty-one percent.

435
00:47:16.360 --> 00:47:18.078
Hundred motels a year. you do the math.

436
00:47:20.120 --> 00:47:22.555
He's got the same little yellow gloves
White Bull wears.

437
00:47:23.160 --> 00:47:25.151
- Is that an Indian thing?
- I guess.

438
00:47:31.160 --> 00:47:33.436
It's good.

439
00:47:34.120 --> 00:47:36.236
That's Steve fucking Jobs good.

440
00:47:37.040 --> 00:47:40.192
I see one flaw. Quality control.

441
00:47:40.280 --> 00:47:42.874
I'm paying her 20 bucks.
I'm not asking for Miss America.

442
00:47:43.880 --> 00:47:48.670
Still. there's no way there's 31 maids
in the whole country worth banging.

443
00:47:48.800 --> 00:47:50.950
You'd be surprised.

444
00:47:56.760 --> 00:47:58.159
Oh dear.

445
00:48:01.160 --> 00:48:03.197
Been at it all night.
haven't gotten a thing out of him.

446
00:48:06.240 --> 00:48:07.230
And you won't.

447
00:48:12.720 --> 00:48:13.710
You know. pain...

448
00:48:17.080 --> 00:48:19.196
it's like a religion to these guys.

449
00:48:19.280 --> 00:48:21.271
You know. the Apaches used
to consider getting tortured

450
00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:22.270
a mark of honor.

451
00:48:22.360 --> 00:48:23.794
How's that for a value system?

452
00:48:23.920 --> 00:48:24.990
He's a Ute.

453
00:48:25.720 --> 00:48:29.031
- What now?
- Local Indians are Utes. Not Apache.

454
00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:32.158
You know I married an Indian.
Don't you think I know the difference?

455
00:49:23.080 --> 00:49:24.753
This doesn't happen in Kehoe.

456
00:49:27.680 --> 00:49:28.954
It just did.

457
00:49:56.440 --> 00:49:57.999
It was his first run.

458
00:50:01.880 --> 00:50:04.156
"Just one run. Papa." he says to me.

459
00:50:07.640 --> 00:50:08.630
"L can do it."

460
00:50:11.440 --> 00:50:12.430
"I'm your son."

461
00:50:12.760 --> 00:50:14.034
What are we going to do?

462
00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:32.832
Okay.
let's go home to Denver.

463
00:51:09.120 --> 00:51:10.349
Mr. Coxman.

464
00:51:22.760 --> 00:51:24.194
I'm very sorry for your loss.

465
00:51:28.120 --> 00:51:29.155
Thanks.

466
00:51:34.640 --> 00:51:35.630
Hey.

467
00:51:36.720 --> 00:51:37.710
So...

468
00:51:38.440 --> 00:51:39.874
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

469
00:51:40.480 --> 00:51:44.314
Ex-boyfriend of mine works Vice in Denver.
So I gave him a call today.

470
00:51:44.800 --> 00:51:47.474
Because you missed him and wanted to see
how he was doing.

471
00:51:47.720 --> 00:51:49.870
Well. he still thinks
there's a chance for us.

472
00:51:50.000 --> 00:51:50.990
What's his name?

473
00:51:52.920 --> 00:51:53.910
Kurt.

474
00:51:55.960 --> 00:51:59.237
- How long were you two lovers?
- Oh. Jesus. Two months. okay.

475
00:52:01.200 --> 00:52:04.716
I had him look up the forensics
on our sign hanger.

476
00:52:05.280 --> 00:52:07.476
The guy's name is Simon Legrew.

477
00:52:08.000 --> 00:52:10.150
Now. his father is White Bull.

478
00:52:10.240 --> 00:52:12.834
He's a Native American
drug dealer from Denver

479
00:52:12.920 --> 00:52:15.275
who's been dealing coke
around here for 30 years.

480
00:52:16.000 --> 00:52:19.152
So now. White Bull
shares territory with Viking.

481
00:52:19.280 --> 00:52:22.830
He's a Denver drug dealer whose real name
is Trevor Calcote.

482
00:52:23.800 --> 00:52:24.790
So...

483
00:52:25.400 --> 00:52:26.390
I'm thinking...

484
00:52:26.800 --> 00:52:28.711
what we have here is a turf war.

485
00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:31.195
A drug turf war.

486
00:52:32.320 --> 00:52:33.549
Right here in Kehoe.

487
00:52:36.240 --> 00:52:37.674
So what are we gonna do about it?

488
00:52:42.600 --> 00:52:48.152
Well. my 30 years' experience tells me
that this is a job for Denver Vice.

489
00:52:48.240 --> 00:52:52.632
It doesn't bother you that I just learned
more about a local drug lord

490
00:52:52.720 --> 00:52:55.519
in five minutes on the phone
than you've learned in 30 years?

491
00:52:55.840 --> 00:52:58.559
What bothers me is that Kurt's
lying in bed tonight

492
00:52:59.160 --> 00:53:01.231
convinced that he's back in your heart.

493
00:53:06.960 --> 00:53:07.950
Kurt's a big boy.

494
00:53:09.320 --> 00:53:10.594
I knew you'd be back.

495
00:53:12.960 --> 00:53:16.430
All right. Viking's real name
is Trevor Calcote.

496
00:53:16.520 --> 00:53:19.080
If you want him dead. you're gonna have to
hire a hit man.

497
00:53:19.160 --> 00:53:21.390
- A hit man?
- Yeah. An assassin.

498
00:53:23.520 --> 00:53:24.669
Do you know one?

499
00:53:25.440 --> 00:53:26.475
The Eskimo.

500
00:53:29.720 --> 00:53:30.835
So. how does this work?

501
00:53:31.840 --> 00:53:35.117
You buy The Eskimo a train ticket.
He's afraid to fly.

502
00:53:35.800 --> 00:53:39.077
You pick him up at the train station.
you drive him to a motel

503
00:53:39.160 --> 00:53:41.117
where you give him half the money upfront.

504
00:53:41.440 --> 00:53:42.430
And then you go home.

505
00:53:44.280 --> 00:53:47.318
<i>- How do</i> I <i>know when it's done?
- Keep checking The Denver Post.</i>

506
00:53:47.400 --> 00:53:48.993
They can't resist a good rub out.

507
00:53:50.720 --> 00:53:54.634
What is it with all these nicknames?
Speedo. Viking. Eskimo.

508
00:53:55.640 --> 00:53:57.551
The Eskimo. It's a gangster thing.

509
00:53:58.200 --> 00:53:59.270
Did you have a nickname?

510
00:54:02.400 --> 00:54:04.516
Yeah. Wingman.

511
00:54:05.960 --> 00:54:06.950
Wingman?

512
00:54:08.240 --> 00:54:11.119
Yeah. from Top <i>Gun.</i>
As in "you can be my Wingman."

513
00:54:15.040 --> 00:54:16.030
Wingman.

514
00:54:35.840 --> 00:54:37.160
Come on.

515
00:54:41.680 --> 00:54:42.670
I tried. buddy.

516
00:55:19.560 --> 00:55:22.074
