Mr. Coxman.

766
01:15:58.880 --> 01:15:59.915
What can I do for you?

767
01:16:02.800 --> 01:16:03.790
It's about your son.

768
01:16:10.240 --> 01:16:12.356
I didn't know if you'd heard
about Dante Ferstel.

769
01:16:12.440 --> 01:16:14.750
Yeah. He died of an overdose.

770
01:16:18.200 --> 01:16:21.511
Dante worked with your son
at the airport. right?

771
01:16:24.160 --> 01:16:25.673
- Yeah.
- Did you know him?

772
01:16:27.040 --> 01:16:28.110
No.

773
01:16:28.200 --> 01:16:29.599
Kyle never mention him to you?

774
01:16:31.000 --> 01:16:31.990
No.

775
01:16:39.160 --> 01:16:40.150
Is that it?

776
01:16:41.680 --> 01:16:42.670
I guess it is.

777
01:16:49.040 --> 01:16:51.077
I don't understand why you're here.

778
01:16:52.280 --> 01:16:53.270
Truth?

779
01:16:54.880 --> 01:16:56.518
I don't think your son was a junkie.

780
01:16:59.480 --> 01:17:01.551
And I don't think
Dante Ferstel was either.

781
01:17:03.680 --> 01:17:05.751
So. what do you think happened to them?

782
01:17:06.760 --> 01:17:07.750
I don't know.

783
01:17:09.080 --> 01:17:12.516
I was hoping you might be able
to tell me something that could help.

784
01:17:17.360 --> 01:17:18.316
Sorry...

785
01:17:19.840 --> 01:17:20.830
I can't help you.

786
01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:24.594
You can't help me. I got work to do.

787
01:17:27.880 --> 01:17:28.870
I understand.

788
01:17:30.480 --> 01:17:31.470
Tape.

789
01:17:32.480 --> 01:17:33.470
Taser.

790
01:17:34.400 --> 01:17:35.470
Antibiotics.

791
01:17:36.160 --> 01:17:37.150
Antibiotics?

792
01:17:37.960 --> 01:17:39.598
Yeah. you ever been bitten by a kid?

793
01:17:41.800 --> 01:17:44.952
Little bastards are nasty. You almost wish
you were bitten by a dog.

794
01:17:49.360 --> 01:17:50.350
Yes?

795
01:17:57.560 --> 01:17:58.880
We can't grab him yet.

796
01:17:59.480 --> 01:18:02.871
- Why not?
- They're sending a messenger.

797
01:18:12.520 --> 01:18:13.919
I am the messenger.

798
01:18:26.080 --> 01:18:27.514
Thank you for seeing me.

799
01:18:34.880 --> 01:18:38.555
He's been punished for his deed.
We want peace with you again.

800
01:18:43.280 --> 01:18:44.679
I appreciate the gift.

801
01:18:46.200 --> 01:18:47.190
It was thoughtful.

802
01:18:54.400 --> 01:18:56.710
You showed a lot of guts
coming here alone.

803
01:19:02.040 --> 01:19:04.031
But I need a son for a son.

804
01:19:41.360 --> 01:19:42.919
Careful. man! You might hit a kid.

805
01:19:48.840 --> 01:19:50.319
If you do it again. I'll kill you.

806
01:19:50.400 --> 01:19:51.913
Yes?

807
01:19:52.960 --> 01:19:55.110
- See you guys tomorrow.
- Hey. Ryan.

808
01:19:55.720 --> 01:19:57.791
Um. I'm taking you home today.

809
01:19:59.280 --> 01:20:01.715
- But this is my mom's week to pick me up.
- Yeah. I know.

810
01:20:01.800 --> 01:20:05.236
but she got stuck at the dentist.
Asked me to come and get you.

811
01:20:05.960 --> 01:20:06.950
What?

812
01:20:08.040 --> 01:20:09.030
We take him.

813
01:20:09.760 --> 01:20:12.479
- What about the messenger?
- We shot the messenger.

814
01:20:13.000 --> 01:20:14.149
I don't remember her telling me

815
01:20:14.240 --> 01:20:17.631
- about a trip to the dentist.
- Yeah. she had a root canal

816
01:20:17.720 --> 01:20:19.040
develop some problems.

817
01:20:21.080 --> 01:20:24.516
And your dad said could I pick you up.
So. here I am.

818
01:20:25.480 --> 01:20:28.472
- This is us here.
- What happened to the Tesla?

819
01:20:33.400 --> 01:20:34.276
Shit!

820
01:21:04.120 --> 01:21:04.951
Seatbelt.

821
01:21:05.040 --> 01:21:07.919
- Where's the kid?
- He got away in a van.

822
01:21:09.080 --> 01:21:10.309
What kind of a van?

823
01:21:11.480 --> 01:21:12.515
Said "Kehoe" on it.

824
01:21:13.400 --> 01:21:16.995
We'll find the kid. We'll find the van.
It won't take us long.

825
01:21:17.080 --> 01:21:19.913
Get rid of these two
before they start to stink.

826
01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:33.990
Answer the phone.

827
01:21:43.160 --> 01:21:44.150
Hello?

828
01:21:47.040 --> 01:21:49.793
No. he can't talk right now.

829
01:21:51.920 --> 01:21:52.910
Because he's dead.

830
01:21:55.880 --> 01:21:58.076
Let's go. Three cars.

831
01:21:58.480 --> 01:21:59.470
What about the body?

832
01:22:03.760 --> 01:22:05.876
Minya. take care of this.

833
01:22:06.800 --> 01:22:09.394
I'm busy. Let the fucking Indian do it.

834
01:22:23.280 --> 01:22:25.112
You don't work for my father. do you?

835
01:22:30.440 --> 01:22:32.272
Who were those guys anyways?

836
01:22:33.120 --> 01:22:34.110
I don't know.

837
01:22:37.840 --> 01:22:39.353
You don't have to worry about them.

838
01:22:40.400 --> 01:22:41.390
Right.

839
01:22:45.680 --> 01:22:47.512
They can't take my son and not call.

840
01:22:48.800 --> 01:22:50.120
That's not how it's done.

841
01:22:52.800 --> 01:22:54.359
Those tepee asswipes.

842
01:22:56.320 --> 01:22:57.833
Those goddamn alkies.

843
01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:01.795
I'm gonna take one of them.

844
01:23:01.880 --> 01:23:04.599
I'm gonna hang them from every
road sign from here to Utah.

845
01:23:05.920 --> 01:23:08.799
You take a man's son. you call!
Everybody knows that!

846
01:23:13.320 --> 01:23:14.549
I mean. they took my boy.

847
01:23:16.080 --> 01:23:17.832
My little boy.

848
01:23:18.120 --> 01:23:20.430
Are you insane! This is my week.

849
01:23:20.520 --> 01:23:22.033
You pick him up without asking?

850
01:23:22.440 --> 01:23:25.034
Are you so damn stupid
you'd kidnap your own son?

851
01:23:26.160 --> 01:23:28.800
I can't wait to watch my lawyer
write up the new arrangement.

852
01:23:29.080 --> 01:23:30.070
Full custody.

853
01:23:31.600 --> 01:23:33.511
You'll be lucky to get him
two hours a month.

854
01:23:33.600 --> 01:23:34.795
Two supervised hours.

855
01:23:35.200 --> 01:23:37.157
A cop in the room with you.
watching you play.

856
01:23:37.280 --> 01:23:39.317
You won't get him alone until
he graduates from high school.

857
01:23:39.400 --> 01:23:42.677
A public high school! With normal kids.
And no stupid diets!

858
01:23:47.160 --> 01:23:50.198
I guess you won't be doing that again.

859
01:23:51.360 --> 01:23:54.034
Right? Uh-huh.

860
01:23:58.080 --> 01:23:59.070
He's not here.

861
01:24:01.200 --> 01:24:03.032
- W hat?
- Ah...

862
01:24:04.280 --> 01:24:07.910
<i>♪ Oh. let's fly
Baby. let's fly away ♪</i>

863
01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:11.152
<i>♪ Across tropical seas ♪</i>

864
01:24:11.760 --> 01:24:14.991
<i>♪ We'll have fun
Underneath the sun ♪</i>

865
01:24:15.320 --> 01:24:18.631
<i>♪ So. come on. baby. please ♪</i>

866
01:24:19.320 --> 01:24:20.310
Turn that song off.

867
01:24:27.160 --> 01:24:30.198
It's a text. From a different number.

868
01:24:31.920 --> 01:24:35.276
"Sequoia Motel. Room twelve."

869
01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:37.718
"Steve Jobs. baby."

870
01:24:55.600 --> 01:24:56.590
Hello.

871
01:25:02.320 --> 01:25:03.549
A little peepee tepee.

872
01:25:36.200 --> 01:25:37.679
Oh. shit.

873
01:25:49.760 --> 01:25:51.433
I know how this world works.

874
01:25:51.520 --> 01:25:53.989
They call with their demands.
I give them what they want.

875
01:25:54.280 --> 01:25:55.475
We get Ryan back.

876
01:25:58.160 --> 01:25:59.434
In 24 hours.

877
01:26:00.840 --> 01:26:01.830
I call the police.

878
01:26:01.920 --> 01:26:04.230
In 24 hours. he'll be home.

879
01:26:04.880 --> 01:26:06.712
- You'll burn in hell for this.
- Yeah.

880
01:26:07.640 --> 01:26:08.630
I'll see you there.

881
01:26:58.440 --> 01:27:00.716
Welcome to Kehoe Chateau Montclair.

882
01:27:00.800 --> 01:27:04.031
- We need rooms tonight.
- I'm sorry. you need a reservation.

883
01:27:04.720 --> 01:27:05.790
Excuse me.

884
01:27:06.520 --> 01:27:07.715
A reservation.

885
01:27:09.160 --> 01:27:10.150
Really?

886
01:27:12.280 --> 01:27:16.672
A reser... Oh! No.
I didn't mean it like that.

887
01:27:16.760 --> 01:27:19.912
I meant you need to reserve...
book before you get here

888
01:27:20.000 --> 01:27:21.877
because we're all full.
That's all I meant.

889
01:27:22.280 --> 01:27:23.429
You know what I heard?

890
01:27:24.000 --> 01:27:25.354
You told me and my friends

891
01:27:25.440 --> 01:27:28.114
that we need to go back
to the reservation.

892
01:27:28.200 --> 01:27:29.190
Oh. no.

893
01:27:30.400 --> 01:27:33.677
Do you have any idea
what I can do to you...

894
01:27:34.680 --> 01:27:35.670
On Yelp?

895
01:27:38.000 --> 01:27:39.752
You might wanna get your boss out here.

896
01:27:40.520 --> 01:27:42.830
Or you could take another look.

897
01:27:44.920 --> 01:27:46.513
I will take another look.

898
01:27:59.440 --> 01:28:01.238
- You hungry?
- Sure.

899
01:28:06.240 --> 01:28:07.355
Eggs?

900
01:28:15.560 --> 01:28:17.437
- You live here?
- Yeah.

901
01:28:21.560 --> 01:28:22.550
All alone?

902
01:28:24.200 --> 01:28:25.190
Yeah.

903
01:28:27.640 --> 01:28:28.869
You don't have any kids?

904
01:28:31.440 --> 01:28:32.430
No.

905
01:28:50.920 --> 01:28:51.910
You like rock?

906
01:28:53.160 --> 01:28:54.150
I like classical.

907
01:29:12.560 --> 01:29:15.871
It wasn't very smart
bringing me to your house.

908
01:29:18.120 --> 01:29:19.110
Why?

909
01:29:24.560 --> 01:29:25.959
I want to talk to your dad.

910
01:29:27.160 --> 01:29:28.150
Tonight?

911
01:29:29.000 --> 01:29:29.990
In the morning.

912
01:29:39.480 --> 01:29:42.313
They're a bit greasy.

913
01:29:52.240 --> 01:29:54.390
You said you didn't have any kids.

914
01:29:55.240 --> 01:29:56.674
He went away.

915
01:29:57.640 --> 01:29:58.835
Go on. get in bed.

916
01:30:04.040 --> 01:30:05.360
Where are you gonna sleep?

917
01:30:06.320 --> 01:30:08.675
In my room. down the hall.

918
01:30:08.760 --> 01:30:11.798
- What if I run away?
- There's nowhere for you to go. kid.

919
01:30:12.160 --> 01:30:14.595
You'd freeze to death out there.
Goodnight.

920
01:30:14.720 --> 01:30:16.791
I always get read a story before bed.

921
01:30:17.400 --> 01:30:18.799
I don't know any stories.

922
01:30:19.160 --> 01:30:21.629
You can read me anything.
I don't care what it is.

923
01:30:25.840 --> 01:30:29.435
The new 6-130 is the creme de la creme
of snow-pushers.

924
01:30:30.160 --> 01:30:33.994
Built to humble Mother Nature.
she has a rated load of three tons.

925
01:30:34.080 --> 01:30:39.393
The Qveraasen UTV attachment
snow blowers are made for universal use.

926
01:30:39.480 --> 01:30:41.835
equipped with powerful modern engines.

927
01:30:42.200 --> 01:30:44.316
They're extremely effective and flexible.

928
01:30:45.360 --> 01:30:48.591
A capacity of four thousand tons
of snow per hour.

929
01:30:50.040 --> 01:30:51.997
Throwing distance of a hundred feet.

930
01:30:54.120 --> 01:30:55.110
Yeah.

931
01:30:56.360 --> 01:30:58.078
She is a great machine. all right.

932
01:30:59.080 --> 01:31:00.070
I've got one of these.

933
01:31:01.800 --> 01:31:03.279
I thought you were a kidnapper.

934
01:31:05.600 --> 01:31:06.590
Not all the time.

935
01:31:08.720 --> 01:31:11.155
Well. can I get a ride in it?

936
01:31:14.080 --> 01:31:15.354
You are going to sleep.

937
01:31:31.560 --> 01:31:34.712
Have you heard of the Stockholm Syndrome?

938
01:32:23.360 --> 01:32:24.475
Morning. boss.

939
01:32:25.480 --> 01:32:26.470
Did you find him?

940
01:32:27.520 --> 01:32:29.875
Not yet. We will.

941
01:32:29.960 --> 01:32:31.280
Mr. White Bull.

942
01:32:32.040 --> 01:32:34.680
These are some complimentary ski passes.

943
01:32:34.760 --> 01:32:38.037
Good for the whole weekend.
For you and all of your... friends.

944
01:32:38.640 --> 01:32:41.951
And I just wanna thank you again
for choosing to stay with us.

945
01:32:42.040 --> 01:32:44.873
We know that you do have
other entertainment options.

946
01:32:47.480 --> 01:32:48.470
Thank you.

947
01:32:50.080 --> 01:32:52.913
- Janitor from Ryan's school.
- Janitor. why not?

948
01:32:53.520 --> 01:32:56.319
It's an honor to be here.
You hear the whispers but...

949
01:32:58.120 --> 01:32:59.997
- You have something for me?
- I might.

950
01:33:02.120 --> 01:33:04.794
The van your boy got into.
I've seen it before.

951
01:33:06.160 --> 01:33:08.720
And the guy that was driving
that van. I've seen him too.

952
01:33:08.800 --> 01:33:12.191
Me and my family go
up to the resort in Kehoe.

953
01:33:12.440 --> 01:33:13.510
You know. the fancy one?

954
01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:15.559
- Chateau Montclair.
- Oh. yeah.

955
01:33:15.640 --> 01:33:19.156
Well. we're driving up and. you know.
she scoots over and she's...

956
01:33:19.480 --> 01:33:23.678
showing a little appreciation
on the way up. you get my drift?

957
01:33:24.160 --> 01:33:25.389
- I do.
- Yeah.

958
01:33:25.760 --> 01:33:27.990
You ever tried to keep the wheel
straight when someone's...

959
01:33:28.120 --> 01:33:29.110
The van.

960
01:33:33.360 --> 01:33:36.716
Well. like I was saying.
The van that stopped to help me...

961
01:33:38.800 --> 01:33:40.837
that's the same van
that your boy got into.

962
01:33:41.760 --> 01:33:44.149
And the guy who pulled me
out of the ditch that night...

963
01:33:45.360 --> 01:33:47.192
he's the same guy that picked up your boy.

964
01:33:47.640 --> 01:33:49.995
He's got one of those names
that you never ever forget.

965
01:33:51.320 --> 01:33:52.310
Coxman.

966
01:33:54.080 --> 01:33:55.070
Coxman.

967
01:33:55.840 --> 01:33:58.593
Yeah. We laughed about it all night long.

968
01:33:59.320 --> 01:34:01.755
- Because what she was doing...
- Oh my God.

969
01:34:02.920 --> 01:34:06.993
- Coxman had a relative.
- And he hasn't spoken with the cops.

970
01:34:07.120 --> 01:34:10.272
Well... how much did my guy offer you?

971
01:34:10.520 --> 01:34:11.510
Ten grand.

972
01:34:12.560 --> 01:34:13.880
Ten grand it is.

973
01:35:08.280 --> 01:35:10.157
Hey! Hey. check him out.

974
01:35:10.800 --> 01:35:12.791
You're crazy. Avalanche!

975
01:35:15.840 --> 01:35:17.319
You sure you've done this before?

976
01:35:18.120 --> 01:35:19.440
I was born to fly. white boy.

977
01:35:58.000 --> 01:36:01.391
I have your son.
If you wanna see him alive. come alone.

978
01:36:01.480 --> 01:36:02.959
Yeah. yeah. I know how it's done.

979
01:36:04.200 --> 01:36:05.918
So. how much do you want for him?

980
01:36:06.000 --> 01:36:11.712
We'll talk about that when you get here.
2210 Quarry Road. Kehoe.

981
01:36:12.600 --> 01:36:16.878
I'm just leaving Denver.
It's gonna take me about three hours.

982
01:36:47.440 --> 01:36:48.635
Jesus Christ.

983
01:36:56.320 --> 01:36:57.310
Son of a...

984
01:37:05.400 --> 01:37:08.472
- Hey.
- Hey. Taking a day off?

985
01:37:09.280 --> 01:37:11.840
- Main road could use a plow.
<i>- I'll</i> get to it soon.

986
01:37:14.960 --> 01:37:16.439
My nephew. Visiting.

987
01:37:17.560 --> 01:37:19.710
Must be a comfort
to have family in town.

988
01:37:20.080 --> 01:37:21.718
We saw all the cars at your place.

989
01:37:25.760 --> 01:37:26.750
Yeah.

990
01:37:34.760 --> 01:37:35.989
Look at this.

991
01:37:37.520 --> 01:37:39.397
- So now we know he's banging a hippie.
- No.

992
01:37:39.760 --> 01:37:41.910
On the truck. The company name.

993
01:37:43.560 --> 01:37:46.074
- Open Road.
- It's four miles away.

994
01:37:47.720 --> 01:37:49.154
- Get the men.
- Let's go.

995
01:37:59.320 --> 01:38:01.630
- That was so much fun!
- I need you...

996
01:38:02.840 --> 01:38:03.830
to sit here...

997
01:38:05.120 --> 01:38:07.031
and wait till someone comes to get you.

998
01:38:21.240 --> 01:38:22.833
<i>They're headed
to Open Road Garage.</i>

999
01:38:22.920 --> 01:38:23.751
Again. Say what?

1000
01:38:25.800 --> 01:38:27.313
Open Road Garage.

1001
01:38:29.920 --> 01:38:30.910
<i>On Old Bend Road.</i>

1002
01:39:04.360 --> 01:39:05.236
Ryan!

1003
01:39:05.800 --> 01:39:08.440
Come on. Inside. Come on. move.

1004
01:39:08.520 --> 01:39:11.672
- Why do you have a rifle?
- Just do what I say. Up the stairs. move.

1005
01:39:13.440 --> 01:39:14.510
Get in the cabinet.

1006
01:39:17.720 --> 01:39:19.119
Why are you mad at me?

1007
01:39:20.040 --> 01:39:22.759
I'm not mad at you. It's just...

1008
01:39:22.840 --> 01:39:24.956
It's just really important
you do what I say.

1009
01:39:27.200 --> 01:39:28.190
You're a good kid.

1010
01:39:29.440 --> 01:39:31.351
- What?
- I said don't move.

1011
01:41:16.200 --> 01:41:17.918
The last Coxman.

1012
01:41:23.440 --> 01:41:25.909
Where is my son?

1013
01:41:28.640 --> 01:41:32.349
My business can get very creative. but I'm
an old fashioned kind of guy.

1014
01:41:32.480 --> 01:41:33.879
I like to keep things simple.

1015
01:41:35.280 --> 01:41:39.433
So if I have to ask you again.
I'm gonna pull out your fingernails...

1016
01:41:40.000 --> 01:41:43.231
cut off your fingers.
chop off your hands...

1017
01:41:43.840 --> 01:41:45.513
and hack off your nose.

1018
01:41:49.920 --> 01:41:51.638
Oh. and that part about the nose.

1019
01:41:51.720 --> 01:41:53.996
you are really not gonna like that part.

1020
01:41:54.320 --> 01:41:56.038
You don't deserve your son.

1021
01:41:59.480 --> 01:42:00.595
Take him to the garage.

1022
